<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="examples">
<div class="example">

  <p>The following example is correct usage of the <code><a href="#the-br-element">br</a></code>
  element:</p>

   <pre><![CDATA[<p>P. Sherman<br>
42 Wallaby Way<br>
Sydney</p>]]></pre>

  </div>
<div class="example">

   <p>The following examples are non-conforming, as they abuse the
   <code><a href="#the-br-element">br</a></code> element:</p>

   <pre><![CDATA[<p><a ...>34 comments.</a><br>
<a ...>Add a comment.<a></p>]]></pre>

   <pre><![CDATA[<p>Name: <input name="name"><br>
Address: <input name="address"></p>]]></pre>

   <p>Here are alternatives to the above, which are correct:</p>

   <pre><![CDATA[<p><a ...>34 comments.</a></p>
<p><a ...>Add a comment.<a></p>]]></pre>

   <pre><![CDATA[<p>Name: <input name="name"></p>
<p>Address: <input name="address"></p>]]></pre>

   <!-- XXX should have labels in the examples above -->

  </div>

</div>
